lass switching","Enhances T cell proliferation"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAnti-inflammatory cytokines play a crucial role in regulating immune responses and preventing excessive inflammation. Interleukin-10 (IL-10) is one of the most important anti-inflammatory cytokines.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe primary function of interleukin-10 is the \u003Cstrong\u003Esuppression of pro-inflammatory cytokine production\u003C/strong\u003E. IL-10 inhibits the synthesis of pro-inflammatory mediators like tumour necrosis factor alpha, interleukin-1, and interleukin-6 from immune cells such as macrophages. This helps resolve inflammation and maintain immune homeostasis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates neutrophil recruitment\u003C/strong\u003E - This is actually a function of pro-inflammatory cytokines like IL-8\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPromotes antibody class switching\u003C/strong\u003E - This is primarily mediated by cytokines like IL-4 and transforming growth factor beta\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases natural killer cell activity\u003C/strong\u003E - Natural killer cells are typically activated by pro-inflammatory cytokines like IL-12 and interferon gamma\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnhances T cell proliferation\u003C/strong\u003E - IL-10 generally suppresses T cell responses rather than enhancing them\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIL-10 is produced by regulatory T cells and alternatively activated macrophages to dampen immune responses and prevent tissue damage from excessive inflammation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Interleukin-10 is a key anti-inflammatory cytokine that suppresses pro-inflammatory cytokine production.","Anti-inflammatory cytokines help resolve inflammation and prevent excessive immune responses.","Interleukin-10 is produced by regulatory T cells and macrophages to maintain immune homeostasis."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019","Hall J. Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology. 14th ed. Elsevier Health Sciences; 2021"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94529"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18760"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94529","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/94529"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-01T20:17:54+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-01T20:17:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11492"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112497"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"rela